An Olympic gold medal won by Jesse Owens at the infamous 1936 Berlin games is up for auction.

The American track star’s domination of multiple events infuriated German Chancellor Adolf Hitler and made him a star.

Mr Owens won four gold medals and set a record in the 100-yard dash during those Olympics.

