Mr Owens worked as a band leader before soon returning home to work for Cleveland’s parks department.

Mr Robinson’s widow’s estate provided the medal for the auction, which is online only.

The whereabouts of the other three original gold medals is unknown.

Mr Owens arrived at the 1936 Olympics as one of many objects of scorn of the hateful dictator Mr Hitler.

The Nazi leader had grand visions of organizing the games to be a showcase of the superior genes and talent possessed by Aryans.

The Germans won a total of 89 medals, the United States’ 56 were second, but it was Mr Owens’ performance that made the German leader throw fits.

